race.comment: YORGA PRIDE (15) had plenty of support in the Jungle Mist Classic last start and wasn't far away, finishing 1.2L off the winner. That form may have been franked in the race prior and Pike sticks with her. Draws to get a similar run in transit and with improvement on the cards out to 1400m now, she looks the one to beat. BONJOY (1) hasn't been far away in the Railway lead-ups, finishing 1.6L off the winner most recently in the Peters. Chris Parnham hops back on board now and her record at this track and trip is solid. Rates highly for a race like this. TOROPA (6) finished off well last start in the Jungle Mist and hit the line alongside YORGA PRIDE. The wide draw is a niggle, but out to 1400m now looks a good move and she'll be finishing with a wet sail. OBJECTIFY (13) was 40-1 in the Jungle Mist but was very good there. Can be in the finish again with third-up. SECRET ATTRACTION (8) can bounce back to her best dropping in trip.
